#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:254
msgid "IDW Interpolation"
msgstr "IDW interpolacija"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:255
msgid ""
"Generates an Inverse Distance Weighted (IDW) interpolation of a point vector"
" layer."
msgstr ""
"Generiše interpolaciju tačkastog vektorskog sloja metodom inverznog "
"ponderisanja rastojanja (IDW)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:258
msgid ""
"Sample points are weighted during interpolation such that the influence of "
"one point relative to another declines with distance from the unknown point "
"you want to create."
msgstr ""
"Uzoračke tačke se ponderišu tokom interpolacije tako da uticaj jedne tačke u"
" odnosu na drugu opada sa rastojanjem od nepoznate tačke koju želite da "
"napravite."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:262
msgid ""
"The IDW interpolation method also has some disadvantages: the quality of the"
" interpolation result can decrease, if the distribution of sample data "
"points is uneven."
msgstr ""
"IDW metod interpolacije ima i neke nedostatke: kvalitet rezultata "
"interpolacije može opasti ako je raspored uzoračkih tačaka neravnomeran."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:266
msgid ""
"Furthermore, maximum and minimum values in the interpolated surface can only"
" occur at sample data points."
msgstr ""
"Osim toga, maksimalne i minimalne vrednosti na interpoliranoj površini mogu "
"se javiti samo u uzoračkim tačkama."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:282
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:546
msgid "**Input layer(s)**"
msgstr "**Ulazni sloj(evi)**"

