msgstr "**Vektorski sloj** [vektor: bilo koji]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:294
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:558
msgid ""
"**Interpolation attribute** [tablefield: numeric]: Attribute to use in the "
"interpolation"
msgstr ""
"**Atribut interpolacije** [tablefield: numerički]: Atribut koji se koristi u"
" interpolaciji"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:296
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:560
msgid ""
"**Use Z-coordinate for interpolation** [boolean]: Uses the layer's stored Z "
"values (Default: False)"
msgstr ""
"**Koristi Z koordinatu za interpolaciju** [logička vrednost]: Koristi "
"sačuvane Z vrednosti sloja (Podrazumevano: False)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:299
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:563
msgid "For each of the added layer-field combinations, a type can be chosen:"
msgstr "Za svaku dodatu kombinaciju sloj-polje može se izabrati tip:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:302
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:566
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Points`: Elevation sample locations containing the values to be "
"interpolated (e.g., terrain height, Z). These points are the primary input "
"for calculating the output surface."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tačke`: Uzoračke lokacije visine koje sadrže vrednosti za "
"interpolaciju (npr. visina terena, Z). Ove tačke su primarni ulaz za "
"računanje izlazne površine."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:305
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:569
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Structured lines`: Lines representing known continuous surface "
"features that guide the terrain shape or structure (e.g., ridges, road "
"centerlines, levees). They describe terrain direction while assuming "
"continuity along the line."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Strukturne linije`: Linije koje predstavljaju poznate neprekidne "
"osobine površine koje usmeravaju oblik ili strukturu terena (npr. grebeni, "
"ose puteva, nasipi). One opisuju pravac terena uz pretpostavku neprekidnosti"
" duž linije."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:308
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:572
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Break lines`: Lines representing known surface discontinuities or"
" hard boundaries (e.g., cliffs, river banks, excavation edges, lake/pond "
"outlines). They mark where the surface may change sharply. It is required if"
" there are significant changes in elevation along the line."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Prelomne linije`: Linije koje predstavljaju poznate "
"diskontinuitete površine ili oštre granice (npr. litice, obale reka, ivice "
"iskopa, obrisi jezera/bara). One označavaju gde se površina može naglo "
"promeniti. Potrebne su ako postoje značajne promene visine duž linije."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:312
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/interpolation.rst:576
msgid ""
"In the string, the layer-field elements are separated by ``'::|::'``. The "
"sub-elements of the layer-field elements are separated by ``'::~::'``."
msgstr ""
"U niski su elementi sloj-polje razdvojeni sa ``'::|::'``. Podelementi "
"elemenata sloj-polje razdvojeni su sa ``'::~::'``."

